  <h1>GBOL5<br>
  <small>Barcoding the German Flora</small></h1>
  <h2>A project of the <a href="http://www.bolgermany.de">German Barcode of Life Initiative</a>
  <a href="http://www.bmbf.de/"><img alt="BMBF" width="100" class="pull-right" src=<%= asset_path('BMBF_transparent.png') %> /></a>
  <small><br>Funded by the <a href="http://www.bmbf.de/">Federal Ministry of Education and Research</a></small></h2>

  <br>
  <p><small>GBOL5 aims to provide a curated reference collection for the approximately 4,800 native land plant species
    (bryophytes, lycophytes, ferns and seed plants) of the German flora with a linkage to specific sequence data (DNA barcodes).
    To ensure identification success, GBOL5 generates sequence data for up to four fast evolving molecular markers from two genomes.</small></p><!--(klick here for more information)-->

  <p><small>GBOL5 is a joint initiative of the <a href="http://www.nees.uni-bonn.de">Nees Institute for Plant Biodiversity
    (NEES, University of Bonn)</a>, the <a href="http://ieb.uni-muenster.de">
    Institute for Evolution and Biodiversity (IEB, University of Münster)</a>,
    the <a href="http://www.bgbm.org/"> Botanical Garden and Botanical Museum Berlin (BGBM, Freie Universität Berlin)</a>
    and the <a href="http://www.naturkundemuseum-bw.de/intl/englisch/stuttgart-state-museum-natural-history"> Stuttgart
    State Museum of Natural History (SMNS)</a>.</small></p>
